caption: This spot never disappoints! Heat lamps have been pumpin for the outdoor seating during pandemic but spring is coming and its heating up! The food is authentic, filling and flavorful. But I dont come here just for the food..drinks get two thumbs up too!

This place is so good! Authentic, delicious food. And the drinks are a great compliment to your meal. We definitely plan to come back again and again to enjoy their margaritas with some tacos. Highly recommend!

Needless to say, the food you eat is magnificent. I have been there more than once and I was always joyful. The rate is modest. I highly suggest this place to my friends and family.

Seeing some of the recent negative reviews makes my heart hurt so I am submitting my 5 star review. The frozen margs here are to die for, they have the best happy hour deals on tuesdays and Wednesday’s, and the food here is so high quality— I have never been disappointed with a dish. Definitely pricier than your average Mexican restaurant but completely worth it for well made, high quality food in my opinion... not sure where the small portion reviews are coming from, I have found the portion sizes to be more than enough. My Mexican fiancé says it’s the best Mexican food he’s ever had in DC and that’s saying something.

Short story:  Chipotle is around the corner. Go there.  Long story:  We finished a trek through the zoo on a hot day and really wanted margaritas and chips & salsa. I found this place via Google Maps. The margaritas were tiny & tasteless, watery even before the ice melted. As soon as the ice started to melt they tasted like those gross La Croix things with only the faintest hint of any flavor. They do not offer complimentary chips and salsa which is fine. I don’t mind paying a few dollars for it but theirs is $10. That also has queso and guacamole which we didn’t want. $10 is nuts. We instead got a couple of tacos. These were ok but not great considering it was $14 for two. It was the one tortilla affair that immediately breaks in half at the bottom and has to be eaten like an open-face sandwich.
I have always loved the happy hour here. If you like things spicy, definitely try their spicy margarita. They also have outdoor seating which is always a plus!

I recommend the queso fundido, the esquites, and the salmon. I also recommend the jalapeno margarita and the churros (so good!).  The service is always friendly, professional and quick. Mayahuel Cocina Mexicana is Mexican restaurant located in Woodley Park neighborhood. My friends and I stopped by mainly for drinks but ended up sharing an order of Platanitos Maduros. The Platanitos Maduros consisted of pan fried sweet plantains topped with salsa chignon, crema, queso, cojita, and cilantro. It was an interesting twist on how plantains are typically served. There was a hint of spice.  Each of us got a drink - House Margarita, Chamomile Infused Tequila Tea, Peach Guava Tequila Punch. Among the drinks, I enjoyed the Chamomile Infused Tequila Tea the most due to its combination of flavors and how innovative/creative the drink was. The seasonal punch was rather bubbly, bitter, and sour.  We hope to return soon to try other Mexican inspired dishes and other specialty cocktails in the near future.
